  "text": "The liberated O 2 of the diatom sample is separated of byproducts in cold traps and directed to a molecular sieve. From the molecular sieve the sample enters a PDZ Europa 2020 mass spectrometer (MS-2020; now supplied by Sercon Ltd., UK) for oxygen isotope analysis at the Isotope laboratory of the Alfred Wegener [CITATION_1] . In general, every fifth sample is a biogenic standard used to verify the quality of the analyses. For the Lake Kotokel series the working standard BFC (a diatomite from Shasta County California) was used ",
